oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.patterns.ui.behaviors
Class SearchSuggestGroupOption

java.lang.Object
  oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.patterns.ui.behaviors.SearchSuggestGroupOption
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public final class SearchSuggestGroupOption
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

A simple class for defining a Search Suggest Group for use in the fnd:SearchSuggestBehavior tag as a list item bound to the groups attribute. This class is immutable.

Since:
11.1.1.7.2

public SearchSuggestGroupOption(java.lang.String groupCreationExpression,

Create the option.

Parameters:
groupCreationExpression - The name of the group. Required. This may be one of the pre-defined groups, or an EL expression to a managed bean that creates the group.
groupHeading - The switch to turn heading on or off for this group. Required.
iconURL - the icon url to use in the heading, if headings are turned on.
groupDisplayName - the display name of the group, over-rides the name defined in SearchSuggestGroup.getDisplayName();
contextCode - possibly null context code for the group.
objectType - possibly null object type for the group.

Create the option.

Parameters:
groupCreationExpression - The name of the group. Required. This may be one of the pre-defined groups, or an EL expression to a managed bean that creates the group.
groupHeading - The switch to turn heading on or off for this group. Required.
iconURL - the icon url to use in the heading, if headings are turned on.
groupDisplayName - the display name of the group, over-rides the name defined in SearchSuggestGroup.getDisplayName();
contextCode - possibly null context code for the group.
objectType - possibly null object type for the group.
enabled - Is this group enabled by default. Users may enable this group at runtime in the UI.

getGroupHeading

public SearchSuggestGroup.GroupHeading getGroupHeading()
Get the group heading switch for this group. If this is on, then the iconURL and displayName can be set, in which case they will over-ride the code defaults of the group.

Note that headings can also be turned off globally in GlobalSearchOptions.
